Humboldt displays interstellar chops at Bridgefest 1 / 2 Back to Gallery gallery_thumbs_close|article-gallery-6414049|article-gallery-6414049|0 gallery_overlay_close|article-gallery-6414049|article-gallery-6414049|0 Bigfoot isn’t the only mysterious creature found in redwood country. Mid-August brings all sorts of extraterrestrials and spacey humanoids to the galaxy-famous Flying Saucer Trials during the annual Bridgefest, gathering on the bridge 45 feet above the Van Duzen River in Bridgeville, a town once put up for sale on eBay. The contest of precision, distance and style is open to all comers who show up with a homemade craft, as are more grounded diversions, such as barbecue and blueberry pie, arts and crafts displays, live music and the new, ever-so-earthy Dirtbag Muster obstacle course.
Vitals: Aug. 15, 10 a.m.-5 p.m. Free. State Highway 36 at Kneeland Road, Bridgeville. (707) 777-1775. www.bridgevillecommunitycenter.org.
Pescadero’s country festival: The Pescadero Art and Fun Festival on the San Mateo coast is this agricultural burg’s juried showcase for local artists and artisans, as well as a fundraiser for local kids’ programs. The festival features home-cooked food sourced from local farmers, music ranging from mariachi to Celtic-country-folk fusion to jam band music, the South Coast Children’s Services Fashion Show, and a kids’ area. Aug. 15-16, 10 a.m.-6 p.m. Free. (650) 879-0848. www.pescaderoartsandfunfestival.org.
Fresno hails the lowly fig: Festivals up and down the state honor nearly every edible substance that grows in the ground, and someone had to take up the cause of the fruit that even Nabisco removed from its Newtons branding in recent years. Cal State Fresno steps up with the California Fig Festival, summoning more than 20 top Central Valley chefs and bakeries to present the highest and best uses of the tasty but not trendy fig. Celebrity chef Fabio Viviani lends his talents to this year’s festival. Aug. 15, 9 a.m.-1 p.m. $25-$45. (559) 243-8600. www.allianceadv.wix.com/californiafigfest.
